header.gameNote: DR PEPPER CLASSIC AT CHATTANOOGA TN

article.headline: Kennesaw St. 78, Alabama St. 72
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Shuan Stegall recorded a double-double, leading Kennesaw State to a 78-72 win over Alabama State in the consolation game of the Dr Pepper Classic on Saturday. Stegall scored 29 points, going 9-for-11 from the free throw line, and grabbed 14 rebounds, including 10 defensive rebounds. Ronell Wooten added another 27 points including six 3-pointers for Kennesaw State (4-10). Moses Edun and Richard Lott Jr. both had 13 points for Alabama State (2-9), and Lott led the team in rebounding with eight grabs. Tremayne Moorer came off the Alabama State bench to score 12 points, and starter Joel Bosh also contributed 10 points. Kennesaw State held its largest lead of 11 points with 11:49 in the first half and led 36-30 at the half. Kennesaw State lost to Chattanooga 83-67 Friday in the first round of the tournament, and Alabama State lost to Colorado State 61-56 in the opening round.
